
[1]dove-tail

   DOVE-TAIL, n. In carpentry, the manner of fastening boards and timbers
   together by letting one piece into another in the form of a doves tail
   spread, or wedge reversed, so that it cannot be drawn out. This is the
   strongest of all the fastenings or jointings.

   DOVE-TAIL, v.t. To unite by a tenon in form of a pigeons tail spread,
   let into a board or timber.
